item.title: Any good free decompilers?
item.dc:creator: @Fridder Fridder
item.description:
@Fridder wrote:

Does anybody know how to make it so when I start up RSBot, it goes online in a certain world, not a random world.
I found in RSLoader:

private JarFile getJar(final String target, final boolean loader) {
	while (true) {
		final int world = 1 + new Random().nextInt(169);
		try {
			final StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder(50);
			sb.append("jar:http://world").append(world).append(".").append(target).append(".com/");
			sb.append(loader ? "loader" : target).append(".jar!/");
			final JarURLConnection juc = (JarURLConnection) new URL(sb.toString()).openConnection();
			juc.setConnectTimeout(5000);
			return juc.getJarFile();
		} catch (final Exception ignored) {
		}
	}

Where it says “final int world = 1 + new Random().nextInt(169);”, I’m guessing the minimum world is 1 and the highest is 169.
If I made it this, would it always start up on world 100?:
final int world = 100;
